<subSubSection id="C3606513FFA8FFA1E9B110BDFE4E5724" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="41" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC53698FFA8FFA1E9B110BDFE4E5724" blockId="40.[683,1212,1118,1728]" lastBlockId="41.[108,636,225,284]" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="41" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">
IDENTIFICATION: We consulted descriptions and measurements of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D1BFFA8FFA0E8F310D8FB0C52E5" baseAuthorityName="Tschudi" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[926,1158,1221,1245]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Sturnira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oporaphilum">
<emphasis id="B90EEA8AFFA8FFA0E8F310D8FB0C52E5" box="[926,1158,1221,1245]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">Sturnira oporaphilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFA8FFA0E87110F6FBB45338" author="Carter, D. C. &amp; P. G. Dolan" box="[796,1086,1256,1280]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" pagination="1 - 136" refId="ref33829" refString="Carter, D. C., and P. G. Dolan. 1978. Catalogue of type specimens of Neotropical bats in selected European museums. Special Publication of the Museum of Texas Tech University 15: 1 - 136." type="journal article" year="1978">Carter and Dolan (1978)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFA8FFA0EF2210F6FD7E531A" author="Anderson, S." pageId="40" pageNumber="40" pagination="1 - 652" refId="ref32736" refString="Anderson, S. 1997. Mammals of Bolivia: taxonomy and distribution. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 231: 1 - 652." type="journal article" year="1997">Anderson (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFA8FFA0E86D1114FBC8531A" author="Velazco, P. M. &amp; B. D. Patterson" box="[768,1090,1290,1314]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" pagination="43 - 66" refId="ref43420" refString="Velazco, P. M., and B. D. Patterson. 2014. Two new species of yellow-shouldered bats, genus Sturnira Gray, 1842 (Chiroptera, Phyllostomidae) from Costa Rica, Panama and western Ecuador. ZooKeys 402: 43 - 66." type="journal article" year="2014">Velazco and Patterson (2014)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFA8FFA0EF121114FCD7537D" author="Molinari, J." pageId="40" pageNumber="40" pagination="75 - 96" refId="ref39655" refString="Molinari, J., et al. 2017. A new polytypic species of yellow-shouldered bats, genus Sturnira (Mammalia: Chiroptera: Phyllostomidae), from the Andean and coastal mountain systems of Venezuela and Colombia. Zootaxa 4243: 75 - 96." type="journal article" year="2017">Molinari et al. (2017)</bibRefCitation>
. No subspecies are currently recognized in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D1BFFA8FFA0E873114EFC37535F" baseAuthorityName="Tschudi" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[798,957,1359,1383]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Sturnira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oporaphilum">
<emphasis id="B90EEA8AFFA8FFA0E873114EFC37535F" box="[798,957,1359,1383]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">S. oporaphilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFA8FFA0E8A41151FD6A53B2" author="Velazco, P. M. &amp; B. D. Patterson" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" pagination="43 - 66" refId="ref43420" refString="Velazco, P. M., and B. D. Patterson. 2014. Two new species of yellow-shouldered bats, genus Sturnira Gray, 1842 (Chiroptera, Phyllostomidae) from Costa Rica, Panama and western Ecuador. ZooKeys 402: 43 - 66." type="journal article" year="2014">Velazco and Patterson, 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFA8FFA0E986116CFC4D53B2" author="Molinari, J." box="[747,967,1394,1418]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" pagination="75 - 96" refId="ref39655" refString="Molinari, J., et al. 2017. A new polytypic species of yellow-shouldered bats, genus Sturnira (Mammalia: Chiroptera: Phyllostomidae), from the Andean and coastal mountain systems of Venezuela and Colombia. Zootaxa 4243: 75 - 96." type="journal article" year="2017">Molinari et al., 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Our specimen exhibits the diagnostic characteristics of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D1BFFA8FFA0EF5A118BFD5D53F7" baseAuthorityName="Tschudi" baseAuthorityYear="1844" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Sturnira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oporaphilum">
<emphasis id="B90EEA8AFFA8FFA0EF5A118BFD5D53F7" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">S. oporaphilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: medium size (FA 
<quantity id="4C829B7DFFA8FFA0E8AF11A9FBC853F7" box="[962,1090,1463,1487]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.45" metricValueMax="4.7" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" unit="mm" value="44.5" valueMax="47.0" valueMin="42.0">42–47 mm</quantity>
); shoulder glands (epaulettes) present but weakly defined; metacarpals III and IV subequal in length, but shorter than metacarpal V; upper inner incisors orthodont; lower incisors bicuspidate; and metaconids and entoconids of m1 and m2 poorly defined, forming a continuous sloping ridge (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFA8FFA0E9D912B6FCE250F8" author="Gardner, A. L." box="[692,872,1704,1728]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" pagination="363 - 376" refId="ref35966" refString="Gardner, A. L. 2008 e (&quot; 2007 &quot;). Tribe Sturnirini. In A. L. Gardner (editor), Mammals of South America, vol. 1: Marsupials, xenarthrans, shrews, and bats: 363 - 376. Chicago: University of Chicago Press." type="book chapter" year="2008">Gardner, 2008e</bibRefCitation>
). Measurements of our speci- mens fall within the range of measurements previously reported for the species.
</paragraph>
